


A "rule" is a full block containing a "target", "prerequisites", and "recipe".
A rule is the whole block: target, prerequisites, and recipe together.


Beyond rules and variable assignments:

Directives
- include / -include / sinclude — read other makefiles
- Conditionals: ifeq, ifneq, ifdef, ifndef, else, endif
- define / endef — multi-line variable definitions
- export / unexport — pass variables to sub-makes
- override — override command-line variable assignments
- undefine
- private — prevent a variable from being inherited by prerequisites
- vpath — search paths for prerequisites by pattern

Note that "ifdef" is misnamed.  The semantics are such that its name
ought to be "ifnotempty".

Rule variants
- Pattern rules (%.o: %.c)
- Static pattern rules ($(OBJS): %.o: %.c)
- Suffix rules (.c.o: — old-fashioned, mostly replaced by pattern rules)
- Double-colon rules (target::)

Special targets
- .PHONY, .SUFFIXES, .DEFAULT, .PRECIOUS, .INTERMEDIATE, .SECONDARY, .DELETE_ON_ERROR, .SILENT, .IGNORE, .EXPORT_ALL_VARIABLES, .NOTPARALLEL, .ONESHELL, .SECONDEXPANSION, .POSIX

Comments
- Lines starting with #
